    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAs per this [discussion](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/35165), in v0.11.3 floats were able to have `title` passed. Now, in v0.12.0-dev, title is ignored and floats do not display a title.\n\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.open_float({ title = \"Diagnostics\" })\nvim.lsp.buf.signature_help({ title = \"Signature Help\" })\n```\n\n| Before: | Now: |\n| --------|-------|\n|<img width=\"547\" height=\"92\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2ee10eac-5209-4e38-a410-2de771974c6b\" />|<img width=\"545\" height=\"89\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/be8014f4-c7e7-4a4f-94e8-8fde7dcb1c7a\" />\n|v0.11.3|v0.12.0-dev-905+gd08b265111|\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nInstall latest prerelease version of nvim\nConfigure vim.diagnostic\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config({\n  float = {\n    title = \"Diagnostics\",\n    header = \"\",\n    prefix = \"\",\n  },\n})\n```\nOpen a diagnostic window `<C-w>d`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhile this may be a regression issue (nowhere in the documentation is there any mention of title for `vim.diagnostic.Opts.Float`), I think having titles (and footers) is a beneficial feature for floats.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-905+gd08b265111-Homebrew\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.6\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm2 Build 3.6.20250726-nightly\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
